description.plain:
Marina Kaye (born February 9, 1998) is a French pop singer and song-writer. She had a YouTube channel where she used to post covers of artists such as Katy Perry, Rihanna or even Whitney Houston.
In 2011 -at only 13- she won the French version of ‘Got Talent’. She could have had an album released just after her victory but she decided to take a few years off to grow and to be forgotten by the public who only knew her as the little girl she was when she won.
She finally released her first album entitled Fearless in 2015 and her second album dropped in 2017.

Critics often say that her deep voice, her dark lyrics and the maturity that exudes from her are breathtakingly magnificient- a rough diamond.

Marina Kaye (born February 9, 1998) is a French pop singer and song-writer. She had a YouTube channel where she used to post covers of artists such as Katy Perry, Rihanna or even Whitney Houston.
In 2011 -at only 13- she won the French version of ‘Got Talent’. She could have had an album released just after her victory but she decided to take a few years off to grow and to be forgotten by the public who only knew her as the little girl she was when she won.
She finally released her first album entitled Fearless in 2015 and her second album dropped in 2017.

Critics often say that her deep voice, her dark lyrics and the maturity that exudes from her are breathtakingly magnificient- a rough diamond.

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Sanity, where have you gone?
You leave at night, return at dawn
I fall from grace, here in the dark
Turn the dive into a work of art
I kissed somebody, I don't know her name
My baby saw me, but I felt no shame
I start to fight with anyone who's in
Hurt everybody, but I feel no pain

[Chorus]
I just wanna feel something
I just wanna feel something

[Verse 2]
Hear me now, laugh with the crowd
But inside the silence screaming loud
Touch me now, my body is warm
But inside, I'm frozen to the bone
I held some bodies tried to crush the cold
But I'm not sorry for the hearts I stole
I wish I could give you tears from my eyes
But it seems that I've forgotten how to cry

[Chorus]
I just wanna feel something
I just wanna feel something

[Bridge]
I'm drinking until I'm drunk
I'm sinking until I'm sunk
But nothing I do, nothing I do seems to fill me
I'm bleeding but I'm still numb
I'm wasted but I still run (Still run)
Run right into, run right into what might kill me

[Chorus]
Just to feel something
I just wanna feel something
Just to feel something
(I just wanna feel something)

[Outro]
Sanity, where have you gone?
You leave at night, return at dawn

description.plain:
This a bonus track from the reedition of the album Fearless.

It It is lyrically similar to the song “Dancing With The Devil” and possibly deals with a past romance Marina had.

body.plain:
This a bonus track from the reedition of the album Fearless.

It It is lyrically similar to the song “Dancing With The Devil” and possibly deals with a past romance Marina had.

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
All that is good
Has turned to darkness
Right before my eyes
I believed you could change
But now I listen to my heart

[Pre-Chorus]
I've lost all my innocence
Now you're keepin' your distance
All I can see is what you left behind

[Chorus 1]
We could've had everything, every dream
You crashed before my eyes
But when you closed the door
You gave me strength to finally realize
All of your lies will set me free
You feed the wolf in me

[Verse 2]
So don't you cry
'Cause your tears are wasted
On disbelieving eyes
I have learned to accept
The fact you never really cared

[Pre-Chorus]
Losing my innocence
Now you're keepin' your distance
All I can see is what you left behind

[Chorus 1]
We could've had everything, every dream
You crashed before my eyes
But when you closed the door
You gave me strength to finally realize
All of your lies will set me free
You feed the wolf in me

[Bridge]
For you it sold off yards
For me it's a tragedy
You held me on a string
But I broke free and felt the air

[Chorus 2]
We could've had everything, every dream
You crashed before my eyes
But when you closed the door
You gave me strength to finally realize
I don't need your sympathy, can't you see?
There's really nothing learned
No need for apology, no fair agree
You feed the wolf in me
You feed the wolf in me
You feed the wolf in me
You feed the wolf in me

I really need you to

Coming back to haunt me every night

You could be my mistake
I don't care anyway

Home, home, home

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Lately you've been making me feel sick of myself
Let you under my skin, now I'm naked as hell
On a wave, my hands ain't tight
And I ain't comin' home tonight
Blinding light
Bla bla bla, you straighten me out, you crooked as well
When you buy the hand that feeds you, swallow yourself
By the way, these hands ain't tight
And I ain't comin' home tonight
Blinding light

[Chorus]
With your blinded heart you've been fooling yourself
You ain't getting nowhere with your eyes closed
Blinded heart, got a bittersweet song
You ain't getting nowhere with those eyes

[Post-Chorus 1]
Handing you a candle in the dark
I'm your candlе in the dark

[Verse 2]
You could cry a river with your crocodile tеars
Damn, this must be Groundhog Day, did the same last year
Out of sight and out of mind
So I'm leaving you tonight
Blinding light

[Chorus]
With your blinded heart you've been fooling yourself
You ain't getting nowhere with your eyes closed
Blinded heart, got a bittersweet song
You ain't getting nowhere with those eyes

[Post-Chorus 1]
Handing you a candle in the dark
I'm your candle in the dark

[Chorus]
With your blinded heart you've been fooling yourself
You ain't getting nowhere with your eyes closed
Blinded heart, got a bittersweet song
You ain't getting nowhere with those eyes

[Post-Chorus 2]
Handing you a candle in the dark (You ain't getting nowhere with those eyes)
Handing you a candle in the dark (You ain't getting nowhere with those eyes)
I'm handing you a candle in the dark
But you can see it with your blind, blind heart

annotatable.title: Don't You Talk About Love

songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
You can break me like glass
A million pieces of heart crushed on the floor
The only thing that I ask
If only you could have loved me a little more
Only time can heal
You can turn on a coin
And fool me again with a new disguise
But the dots didn't join
Now I'm finding the truth hidden in your eyes (In your eyes)
I'm learning not to feel (Feel, feel)

[Chorus]
So don't look like you're concerned
We both know that's not true
You haven't figured out
I'm such a part of you
The part that's slipping through your hands (Hands, hands)
Stone is made of sand
Stone is made of sand

[Verse 2]
I learned to keep it inside
Hidden safe in a box deep in my heart
But now I'm ready to smile
A new beginning, it's time to make a start
To rewrite history
To do what's right for me

[Chorus]
So don't look like you're concerned
We both know that's not true
You haven't figured out
I'm such a part of you
The part that's slipping through your hands (Hands, hands)
Stone is made of sand
Stone is made of sand

[Bridge]
I'm falling, I'm praying
I'd wake up and that's all a dream
I'm drowning, I'm waiting
But you're not coming

[Chorus]
So don't look like you're concerned
We both know that's not true
You haven't figured out
I'm such a part of you
The part that's slipping through your hands (Hands, hands)
Stone is made of sand
Stone is made of sand

[Outro]
So don't you talk about love
'Cause anybody can say they love someone

songs.embed_content: Read “Small Beginning” by Marina Kaye on Genius
songs.title: Small Beginning
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I've been searching all my life
For a way to ease the torment
I've been outside and upturned
I've been frozen in the moment
All my ghosts and all my fears
Laying silent now within me
If I could rest just for an hour
Then love could come and free me

[Pre-Chorus]
And I have learned to forgive myself
And I have learned how to trust again

[Chorus]
This is my small beginning
What I am loosing, I am winning
I am the fragments dreams are made from
I am the bridge that love was built on
This is my small beginning

[Verse 2]
Tiny steps upon the earth
Leaving hardly any trace
If I could wake and love myself
Then feel the sun upon my face

[Pre-Chorus]
And I have learned to forgive myself
For everything that I have done

[Chorus]
This is my small beginning
What I am loosing, I am winning
I am the fragments dreams are made from
I am the bridge that love was built on
This is my small beginning

[Bridge]
Maybe a day when I don't question why (Don't question why)
Maybe an hour when there's no need to cry, no need to cry

[Chorus]
This is my small beginning
What I am loosing, I am winning
I am the fragments dreams are made from
I am the bridge that love was built on
This is my small beginning
